cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on optimizing the layouts of mobile user interfaces using neural networks and gradient descent. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since it involves machine learning techniques. The use of neural networks also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the optimization of layouts could also be considered a graphics-related task, placing it under computer graphics (cs.GR).
